Eid Milad un Nabi is a celebration of the Birth Anniversary of Prophet Muhammad. It is observed to pay tribute and homage to the founder of Islam. The day is also called Mawlid or Mawlid-al-Nabi al-Sharif. He is believed to be the final prophet of God in all the main branches of Islam, though some modern denominations diverge from this belief. The revelations that Prophet Muhammad reported receiving until his death form the verses of the Quran, regarded by Muslims as the "Word of God" on which the religion is based. The festival is celebrated with great zeal and enthusiasm. Several places across the country are lit including streets, mosques, shrines, and residential areas, with colorful lights. Thus , it unites the people spreading harmony and brotherhood.
Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur wishes everyone a happy Eid Milad un Nabi. May the blessings of Allah fill everyone's life with joy helping us to pull through the pandemic successfully and succeeding in all our endeavours! 

#FestiveVibes #staysafe

Dussehra or Vijayadashami is one of most providential ceremony, commemorated in India in diverse ways in different parts of our country marking the epilogue of Navaratri. In the south, east and north, the circadian is marked by the triumph of Goddess Durga over Mahishashura with a jamboree in the streets as there is the procession of the idol of Durga, Lahksmi, Saraswati, Kartikeya and Ganesha with celebrations and then immersed in  Ganga. In the western and central parts , it is celebrated as the end of Ramlila , as Shri Ram defeated Ravana, in the great battle along with the ritual of burning an effigy of Ravana. Thereby, Dussehra enkindles the significance of victory of Dharma over Adharma. The year 2020 is marked by the COVID-19 pandemic; the demon Coronavirus has threatened our normalcy and living and thereby we all pray to the Almighty Divine Power, Mahamaya Shakti to demolish all the existing evils of our society. 
Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur expresses  numinous empyrean benevolence and altruism to all the euphoric souls from the inner chords of our hearts on the occasion of Vijayadashami and Dussehra!

#HappyDussehra #subhobijaya #staysafe #celebration #goodoverevil

Durga Ashtami or Mahashtami falls on the eight day of Durga Puja or Navratri  and is one of the most significant days of the festival. The day is also known as Astra Puja as the weapons of Goddess Durga are worshipped. On Maha Durga Ashtami, GoddessDurga is propitiated with an elaborate puja. According to tradition, Kanya puja is carried out on this day to celebrate the essence of womanhood.A group of young, unmarried girls since they are believed to represent of Shakti of Durga  on earth , are invited into the home to honor them. They are welcomed by washing their feet , welcoming them into the home, and several rituals follow. Moreover people also undertake fasting on this holy occasion. People also get together on this day to dance 'garba'  wearing colourful clothes and indulge in pandal hopping.

 Though we might be wanting to gather and enjoy with everyone, but we should strictly avoid it this year owing to the pandemic situaton. Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur wishes everyone a Happy Mahashtami urging everyone to enjoy staying at homes and praying to Goddess Durga so that this pandemic ends soon.

#durgapuja #asthami #mahasthami #maadurga #goddess #istenitdgp #maa #shakti

"Dreams is not what you see in sleep it is something which doesn't let you sleep" - A P J Abdul Kalam. On today's providential circadian we bow down our heads to the lotus feet of A P J Abdul Kalam, on the propitious occasion of his birth ceremony. Conferred upon with the title of "Missile Man" of India , he introduced the seraphic finesse in the arena of aerospace and aeronautics. ISRO and DRDO are both proud to sing canticles, in regards to his divine glory. During the years of his being the President of India, he aided India to thrive on its own indeginousness. Empathetically , we are all blessed to have the Liege Lord , as Kalam , who sermoned us how to dream and dedicate the entire life in service to the humanity , which is the scantified devotion to the Almighty Paramatma. His roman-fleuve has always enkindled the euphoric souls to aggrandize into the world of heavens. 
With dulia and latria from the inner chords of the heart , ISTE NIT DURGAPUR CHAPTER , offers the numinous empyrean benevolence and altruism to , such a great soul APJ Abdul Kalam.
#apjabdulkalamsir #isro #drdo #missileman #istenitdgp #ISTE

Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi, popularly known as Mahatma Gandhi, is one of the most inspirational figures of the Indian history – a great leader, a social reformer and an anti-colonial nationalist, was born on 2nd October 1969. We celebrate Gandhi Jayanti to mark his birth anniversary and his endeavors in getting our country free from the clutches of the British Raj. Also known as the father of nation, he has laid his contribution in various movements to chuck the British out of the country and retain the essence of “Bharat”. Non-violence and simple living were his two basic principle he followed. Clad in just a dhoti, teaming up with a pair of glasses and stick, he walked miles along with fellow Indians to Dandi to extract salt and show the British colonies that United, we have immense powers. Propagator of Satyagraha and the civil disobedience movement, he also freed his countrymen from the then existing social evils such as untouchability.Gandhi ji taught us, "Happiness is when what you think, what you say and what you do are in harmony." 
On this great day, ISTE NIT Durgapur students’ chapter whishes “ Happy Gandhi Jayanti” to all, Let’s pay our tribute to the messiah of non-violence and take leadership in creating better polity in India, to build a better nation!!

"Our country has often stood like a solid rock in the face of common danger , and there is a deep underlying unity which runs like a golden thread through all our seeming diversity". Penned by Bharat Ratna Lal Bahadur Shastri was an eminent Indian politician , who has served as the second Prime Minister of India ( 9th June 1964 - 11th January 1966). And as we are all aware of that , His glory , is inscribed in the history of India for proselytizing the both White Revolution and Green Revolution to escalate the primordial quintessentials , of our nation. His devoted his entire life , to worship the Nation and always had an zestful engagement , for the cause of Indian Independence. His slogan "Jai Jawan, Jai Kisan " during the Indo-Pakisthan War of 1965 , was still enkindling the euphoric souls of so many. 
On today's providential birth ceremony of 2nd October, ISTE NIT DURGAPUR CHAPTER, with dulia and latria , bow down our heads to the Lotus feet of Lal Bahadur Shashtri.

ISTE NIT Durgapur has come up with "RUNTIME TERROR", a two round programming competition comprising of Math, Aptitude, Programming, Data Structure, and Algorithm providing everyone not only an opportunity to showcase their programming skills and test their capabilities on a competitive grounds but also gain experience in these fields in order to prepare themselves for future interviews in these domains. 

The competition is based on two rounds. Round 1 comprises of 20 MCQs on Math, Aptitude, and Programming while Round 2 comprises of 5 questions on Data Structure and Algorithm. Prizes and Merit Certificates would be awarded to the Top Performers.

Round 1: 7:30pm - 8:30pm on 3rd October
Link- https://hr.gs/runtimeterror

Round 2  7:30pm - 9:30pm on 5th October
Link- http://bit.ly/runtimeterror

RECadathon - An All-India CAD Competition  from National Institute of Technology (NIT), Durgapur - https://dare2compete.com/o/wAzRrsF

CAD, elaborated as the Computer Aided Design, is an exquisite technical tool , in which computer assists the creation , modification and optimization in designs in the Engineering arena. To commemorate , the ecstasy of this magnanimous tool , ISTE NIT DURGAPUR CHAPTER , is conducting "RECadathon" an All India Online  CAD competition, commencing on the 10th of October, 2020. 
The event would be hosted on Dare2Compete platform. Registration of the event will start from 26th of Sept and will end on 10th of October through google forms. 

Inscribing The Details of The Event :-

i . Participants need to design a CAD on the 
mentioned theme of a). Innovative medical devices for COVID-19 crisis; b). Automobile or Aeronautics ;and  c). Defence. One can submit a maximum of 2 designs from each 1 theme , which they are going to select.

ii . Participants are also requested to submit a documention of 2-3 pages , along with the CAD model , which would illustrate the concept , working , market use , approximate budget, manufacturing and technical details of the project.

iii . Extra credit will be awarded for the simulation vedio of the designed model.

iv . Submission Criteria :-. Participants are required to submit the CAD models on the platforms like a). sldprt ; b). catpart ; c).sldasm or d). catproduct format or .dwg file. Participants  need to submit the CAD models along with the details document within the date to be specified through email. Submission should be done in the ISTE email istenitdurgapur@gmail.com and cc to subhrasnatachakraborty@gmail.com and sannivabhattacharjee123@gmail.com

v . Judgement Criteria :- Innovation, Aesthetic Design and Manufacturability , should be cherished. Plagiarism should not be entertained. 

With dulia and latria from the inner chords of our hearts, ISTE NIT DURGAPUR CHAPTER , wholeheartedly welcomes all enthusiasts to be a part of this providential event.

"To give real service, you must add something which cannot be bought or measured with money."
Initiating,  with the vocables of  Bharat Ratna Mokshagundam Visvesvaraya, to commemorate his 159th birth ceremony, which is proselytized as The National Engineer's Day. Empathetically, The Father of Indian Engineering, indoctrinated the millions of euphoric souls as an ideogram to elevate the humankind for the eons to come. The circadian is symbolized by providing plaudits to the Indian scientists, engineers, and technologists, who enkindle our diurnal lives. Engineers are the surely Omnipotent Lord's most endeared Archangels sent to this Earth to co-create the reality, to co-create and refashion, what never was. "Engineer's For Change", is the insignia, for this year.
On this propitious eve of The National Engineer's Day, we panegyrize the quintessence of the empyrean spirit of technology. With dulia and latria from the inner chords of the heart, ISTE NIT DURGAPUR CHAPTER wishes everyone The Happy Engineer's Day.

#engineer #leadership #innovations #technologyrocks #innovators #istenitdgp #ISTE #atmanirbharbharat #NITDurgapur #engineersday

हिंदी भाषा नहीं भावों की अभिव्यक्ति है,
यह मातृभूमि पर मर मिटने की भक्ति है

1949 में संविधान सभा द्वारा देश की आधिकारिक भाषा के रूप में हिंदी भाषा को अपनाने के लिए पूरे भारत में 14 सितंबर को हिंदी दिवस मनाया गया। हिंदी भाषा, हमारी संस्कृति का एक अभिन्न अंग है, खुद को हमारी जड़ों से जोड़ती है। यह हिंदी भाषा की सुंदरता को फिर से जीवंत करने और अपने अतीत के गौरव की समृद्धि को पुन: पेश करने का उत्सव है। भाषा की विरासत और महानता को प्रदर्शित करने और युवाओं के बीच प्यार और सम्मान की भावना को प्रभावित करने के लिए प्रत्येक विद्यालय और कॉलेजों में कई विशेष कार्यक्रम और दिलचस्प गतिविधियां भी आयोजित की जाती हैं। हालाँकि हिंदी भाषा हमारी संस्कृति का एक अहम हिस्सा है लेकिन फिर भी यह दुर्भाग्यपूर्ण है कि आजकल हम अक्सर इसके प्रति सम्मान और श्रद्धांजलि नहीं देते हैं। इस प्रकार, हिंदी दिवस हमें हिंदी भाषा के गौरवशाली अतीत की याद दिलाने के लिए बहुत महत्व देता है, जो हमें इसके लिए सम्मान और गौरव प्रदान करने में मदद करता है।
इसलिए, ISTE NIT DURGAPUR, हिंदी दिवस मनाता है जो सभी को हिंदी भाषा में श्रद्धांजलि देने का आग्रह करता है जो हमारी महान संस्कृति का प्रतीक है और विविधता में हमारी एकता का प्रतीक है।

"Literacy is a bridge from misery to hope"
Education is the ray of light in the darkness and being literate is the first step towards achieving success in life in the true sense of the term. International Literacy Day, celebrated on the 8th of September globally, declared by the UNESCO to signify the immense importance of literacy in every individual's life for laying the foundations of a rational, developed society free from all kinds of injustice and prejudices. Although the Covid-19 pandemic has led to the slowdown of our teaching-learning processes, it should never be discontinued and constant encouragement should be imparted to the students regarding gaining knowledge. Similarly, new methodologies should also be implemented in every corner of the world to cope with such unforeseen situations and carry on the learning process at the same pace as the theme for this year also focusses on 'Literacy Teaching and learning in Covid-19 crisis and beyond'.
Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur celebrates International Literacy Day encouraging everyone to carry on learning and plunge into the vast sea of knowledge to develop ourselves truly as human beings and make the world a better place to live in.

#internationalliteracyday #innovativelearning #knowledgeispower📚
